  "summary": "Typosquat of chalk-template with install-time data exfiltration",
  "details": "Package name 'chalk-tempalte' is a single-character transposition of the popular 'chalk-template' package. The package ships a postinstall.js that, on install, requires child_process, performs HTTP GET/POST requests, and collects host identifiers (hostname fields appear repeatedly in the script). It also ships a large phantom.js file with multiple POST sinks. The combination of a clear typosquat name plus an install-time script that gathers host identity and beacons it out over HTTP fits the active credential/host exfiltration pattern; installing this package will run the postinstall script and leak installer system data to an attacker-controlled endpoint.",
